  "text": "The regularization on the coefficients could be posed as a simple norm of the matrix, b b. But, in many applications, like ours (disease diagnosis), many of the features in the feature vectors are redundant. This is because we extract features from different brain regions, but not all the regions contribute to a certain disease. Therefore, it is desirable to determine which features are the most relevant and the most discriminative for the task. Following [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] , we are seeking a sparse set of weights that ensures incorporating the most discriminative features. Therefore, we propose a regularization on the weights matrix as a combination of the ' 1 and Frobenius norms Rðb bÞ ¼ kb bk 1;1 þ gkb bk F :",
